{"id":"math240-lineval-mix001","cid":"MATH 240","topic":"Applications Growth Decay","subtopic":"Exponential growth and decay","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A tank contains Q grams of salt. The rate of change is Q'(t) = {m}Q + {b}. Find Q'(t) when Q = {x_val} grams.","params":{"m":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":15},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":5,"max":20}},"answer_expr":"lineval","steps":["Substitute Q = {x_val}: Q'({x_val}) = {m}·{x_val} + {b} = {m_times_x} + {b} = {answer_lineval} g/min."],"tags":["ode","mixing-problem","rate"]}
